    {
      "title": "Plural Formation - Overview",
      "text": "Slovak plural formation in nominative case varies by gender and the type of consonant ending the noun stem. The patterns are generally predictable once you know the noun's gender and stem type (hard vs. soft consonants).",
      "examples": [
        "Masculine: muž → muži (men)",
        "Feminine: žena → ženy (women)",
        "Neuter: mesto → mestá (cities)"
      ]
    },
